)\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t\tIt(\"should not add the scheduling gate even when the CPPC namespaceSelector matches all namespaces\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-oka-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeSelectors(utils.ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel, \"\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t\tEventually(func(g Gomega) {\n\t\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Get(ctx, crclient.ObjectKeyFromObject(pod), pod)\n\t\t\t\t\tg.Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to get pod\", err)\n\t\t\t\t\tg.Expect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).NotTo(ContainElement(\n\t\t\t\t\t\tcorev1.PodSchedulingGate{Name: utils.SchedulingGateName},\n\t\t\t\t\t), \"scheduling gate should not be added to pods in openshift-kube-apiserver\")\n\t\t\t\t\tg.Expect(pod.Labels).To(HaveKeyWithValue(\n\t\t\t\t\t\tutils.SchedulingGateLabel, utils.LabelValueNotSet,\n\t\t\t\t\t), \"scheduling gate label should be not-set\")\n\t\t\t\t}).Should(Succeed(), \"pod in openshift-kube-apiserver should not be gated\")\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n### What changed\n\nA new `Context` block was added inside the existing `When(\"The scheduling gat mutating webhook\", ...)` block, after the existing `Context(\"is handling the mutation of pods\", ...)`.\n\nThe new context:\n1. **`BeforeEach`**: Creates the `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace using `testingutils.EnsureNamespaces` (same pattern as `suite_test.go:306`).\n2. **`It` block**: Constructs a pod using the fluent builder API with:\n   - A container image from the test registry\n   - `WithGenerateName(\"test-pod-oka-\")` for unique pod names\n   - `WithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\")` — the target namespace\n   - `WithNodeSelectors(utils.ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel, \"\")` — sets `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane: \"\"` in the pod's nodeSelector, which is the standard selector on kube-apiserver pods in OpenShift\n3. **Assertions**: Uses `Eventually` to verify:\n   - The pod does NOT have the scheduling gate `multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate` in `spec.schedulingGates`\n   - The scheduling gate label is set to `\"not-set\"` (confirming the webhook processed the pod but chose to ignore it via `shouldIgnorePod`)\n\n### Why this works\n\nThe webhook's `shouldIgnorePod` returns `true` when `pod.HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` is true. The `HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` method (in `pkg/models/pod.go:134`) checks for `node-role.kubernetes.io/master` or `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane` in the pod's nodeSelector. Kube-apiserver pods in OpenShift always have this selector because they run on control plane nodes. So even though the CPPC's `namespaceSelector` matches all namespaces (the test suite's CPPC has `nil` namespaceSelector, which means no namespace filtering), the pod is still not gated.\n\n### New imports added\n\n- `corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"` — for `corev1.PodSchedulingGate`\n- `testingutils \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/framework\"` — for `EnsureNamespaces`\n- `\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"` — for `SchedulingGateName`, `ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel`, etc.\n- `crclient \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"` — for `ObjectKeyFromObject`\n\n### Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# Run the focused test\nNO_DOCKER=1 GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='openshift-kube-apiserver'\" make unit\n\n# Or run all webhook tests\nNO_DOCKER=1 GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook'\" make unit\n```\n\n**Note on `EnsureNamespaces`**: The `EnsureNamespaces` helper calls `client.Create` and expects no error. If the namespace already exists (e.g., from a prior test run in the same 